{"ts":"2026-06-27T18:18:34.586Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"yvd96gse","input":{"summary":"The task of connecting Admin Projects and AI Operations pages to the backend CRUD endpoints has been completed and verified successfully.\n\nSpecific accomplishments:\n1. **Admin Projects CRUD Connectivity:**\n   - Modified `/app/admin/projects/page.tsx` to utilize `apiClient.projects` methods.\n   - Integrated full list retrieval on page mount, state synchronization, inline state/phase edits, and new project provisioning.\n   - Implemented error handling with high-fidelity local fallback states when the server is offline.\n\n2. **Admin AI Operations CRUD Connectivity:**\n   - Integrated `/app/admin/ai-operations/page.tsx` with `apiClient.aiOperations` endpoints.\n   - Enabled listing telemetry-active enclaves, real-time status and owner modification with persistent backend updates, termination, and new agent creation.\n   - Replaced static initialization list with mapApiToRichAgent transformation logic that maps standard API attributes to custom high-fidelity operational agent stats.\n\n3. **API Client & Auth Sync Integration:**\n   - Updated `/lib/api-client.ts` to seamlessly handle authentication token validation, ensuring bearer tokens sync automatically prior to executing requests.\n\n4. **Testing and Verification:**\n   - Executed both TypeScript compilation check (`npx tsc -p tsconfig.json --noEmit`) and deterministic node tool checks (`npm run verify-tools`), which completed flawlessly.\n   - Ran `node scripts/test-project-apis.js` and `node scripts/test-ai-operations-apis.js` to assert the correctness of API route behavior, yielding complete verification success.","verified":true}}}
